metadata.name: Key World (1/3)
metadata.description:
This edition is for (artist (creator))
1 of 3

You said that people have feelings. They understand art.
I claim the opposite. People form groups and market their artists.
However, artificial intelligence will have an algorithm that is completely on merit in the future.

They will be able to discover anything of value in a matter of seconds, independent of the owner.

The artist will not have to be popular.

I believe that; artificial intelligence will be a much better collector who understands real art.

The extinction of man will be because of these selfish strata.

1 human collector
1 humanoid collector
